column5: Transmission error
column6: Transmission error is  occurred between YRC1000 and laser sensor unit.
column7:
(1)Reset the alarm, and then try again.
(2)Turn off the power of YRC1000 and Laser sensor unit, and turn on. 
(3)Check the connection between connector on JANCD-ACP01 CN105 or CN106 and the cable from laser sensor unit.
(4)Replace JANCD-YCP21 board and the cable.
If the alarm occurs again, save the CMOS.BIN, and then contact your YASKAWA representative about occurrence status (operating procedure).

column5: Input parameter error
column7:
(1) SxE202 needs to be set only when the scale conversion of the measured value used by the digital COMARC function for sensing is required. Enter 0 for SxE202 if you do not need to scale the measurements. If scale conversion of the measured value is required, enter the M register number in SxE202 that stores the measurements used by the digital COMARC function for sensing.
(2) When the set value of SxE202 is other than 0, the set value of SxE200 and SxE201 is used to perform scale conversion of the measured value used by the digital COMARC function for sensing. Enter the minimum measured value in SxE200 and the maximum measured value in SxE201.
(3)If the alarm occurs again, save the CMOS.BIN, and then contact your YASKAWA representative about occurrence status (operating procedure).

column3: An error occurred in the arithmetic process for coordinates in gauging motion.
column5: It is the kind of error of arithmetic process for coordinates.
column7:
(1)When another alarm has occurred at the same time, Take the measures of it, 
(2)When another alarm has not occurred at the same time, Reset the alarm, and then try again.
(3)If the alarm occurs again, save the CMOS.BIN , and then contact your YASKAWA representative about occurrence status (operating procedure).
